Thank you, Ardan.

00:09:03.760 --> 00:09:06.790
So this is a really exciting
opportunity to actually have

00:09:06.790 --> 00:09:08.870
the ability to have your voice,
as well as the voice of

00:09:08.870 --> 00:09:11.550
your users, on your Google
search results page for your

00:09:11.550 --> 00:09:12.640
brand query.

00:09:12.640 --> 00:09:15.160
And that's almost
unprecedented.

00:09:15.160 --> 00:09:16.620
In fact, actually, it
is unprecedented.

00:09:16.620 --> 00:09:18.460
And you might think
to yourself, how

00:09:18.460 --> 00:09:19.390
can I make this happen?

00:09:19.390 --> 00:09:22.120
And the great news is that
it's incredibly easy.

00:09:22.120 --> 00:09:24.210
I'm going to describe today
two different levels of

00:09:24.210 --> 00:09:26.220
integration that you can do.

00:09:26.220 --> 00:09:29.430
One is so simple that within
the span of half an hour's

00:09:29.430 --> 00:09:32.430
worth of time today while
sitting in Google I/O, you can

00:09:32.430 --> 00:09:36.250
get your portion of this ball
rolling to activate the right

00:09:36.250 --> 00:09:37.840
hand search box to begin with.

00:09:37.840 --> 00:09:44.520
All that involves is having an
activated +Page that also has

00:09:44.520 --> 00:09:48.930
current posts that have been
posted quite recently on it.

00:09:48.930 --> 00:09:50.460
The second level of integration
that I'm going to

00:09:50.460 --> 00:09:52.940
describe is integrating
Google+ Sign-In.

00:09:52.940 --> 00:09:56.700
Google+ Sign-In, in turn, as
Ardan mentioned, allows you to

00:09:56.700 --> 00:09:59.910
send activities with the user's
consent to Google,

00:09:59.910 --> 00:10:03.680
which we in turn can pass back
to you in the form of

00:10:03.680 --> 00:10:06.830
promotion in the right hand
search box on the popular

00:10:06.830 --> 00:10:07.950
Google+ box.

00:10:07.950 --> 00:10:09.620
Let's get into the details.

00:10:09.620 --> 00:10:13.210
First level of integration is
what I call basic integration.

00:10:13.210 --> 00:10:15.760
All you need to do to activate
the right hand search box is

00:10:15.760 --> 00:10:20.100
to have a Google+ that you've
created that claims a website

00:10:20.100 --> 00:10:23.255
that corresponds to your
Google+ brand query--

00:10:23.255 --> 00:10:25.460
excuse me, your Google
brand query.

00:10:25.460 --> 00:10:28.990
And then that page in turn will
have validation code on

00:10:28.990 --> 00:10:32.620
at that points back to your
+Page to ensure that the +Page

00:10:32.620 --> 00:10:36.170
is yours and you
are the +Page.

00:10:36.170 --> 00:10:37.500
The second level of
integration is

00:10:37.500 --> 00:10:39.310
to integrate Google+.

00:10:39.310 --> 00:10:43.030
You integrate Google+ to tell us
who is doing activities on

00:10:43.030 --> 00:10:45.690
your site, what those activities
are, and then with

00:10:45.690 --> 00:10:49.430
the help of schema.org, you'll
be able to tell Google's

00:10:49.430 --> 00:10:52.370
search engine more about the
page, such that we can render

00:10:52.370 --> 00:10:55.930
something relevant and
contextual for the user.

00:10:55.930 --> 00:10:58.380
So let's dive right on in.

00:10:58.380 --> 00:11:00.070
First thing to do is
to set up a +Page.

00:11:00.070 --> 00:11:02.360
Many people here have probably
already done so, but if you

00:11:02.360 --> 00:11:04.140
haven't, it's incredibly
simple.

00:11:04.140 --> 00:11:07.540
You simply just go to Home,
Pages, Add a Page, and you'll

00:11:07.540 --> 00:11:09.710
go through a very easy
to follow flow.

00:11:09.710 --> 00:11:11.830
And I'll walk through some of
the most relevant fields

00:11:11.830 --> 00:11:12.610
associated with that.

00:11:12.610 --> 00:11:15.040
There's quite a few others,
many of them quite

00:11:15.040 --> 00:11:16.840
self-explanatory.

00:11:16.840 --> 00:11:19.650
So in this case, we're talking
about a product or a brand in

00:11:19.650 --> 00:11:20.980
terms of classification.

00:11:20.980 --> 00:11:22.680
And you'll give your product
a brand type.

00:11:22.680 --> 00:11:24.500
The two fields that are
most relevant are the

00:11:24.500 --> 00:11:25.560
most obvious ones.

00:11:25.560 --> 00:11:27.470
One is your name--

00:11:27.470 --> 00:11:28.670
pretty straightforward.

00:11:28.670 --> 00:11:32.810
That name will show up directly,
prominently, and in

00:11:32.810 --> 00:11:35.930
large text in the right hand
search box on the top.

00:11:35.930 --> 00:11:38.280
The second is your website.

00:11:38.280 --> 00:11:40.010
The website is what
you were claiming

00:11:40.010 --> 00:11:42.320
corresponds to that +Page--

00:11:42.320 --> 00:11:43.560
pretty straightforward.

00:11:43.560 --> 00:11:47.590
For best results for that +Page,
execute your brand

00:11:47.590 --> 00:11:50.380
query directly yourself, and
simply just copy and paste.

00:11:50.380 --> 00:11:52.750
Make sure that there's a
one-to-one correspondence.

00:11:52.750 --> 00:11:55.140
It might not necessarily be
absolutely required, but to

00:11:55.140 --> 00:11:58.440
make things easy, just
copy the URL directly

00:11:58.440 --> 00:12:01.480
into the claim box.

00:12:01.480 --> 00:12:02.600
That's fairly simple.

00:12:02.600 --> 00:12:06.130
The last stage, which I don't
show on this slide, is simply

00:12:06.130 --> 00:12:07.830
just to have your
profile image.

00:12:07.830 --> 00:12:11.490
The profile image is what
shows up in the top left

00:12:11.490 --> 00:12:14.740
portion of the right
hand search box.

00:12:14.740 --> 00:12:16.080
So that's great.

00:12:16.080 --> 00:12:17.520
At this point, you
have a +Page.

00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:20.000
You've claimed the page
that corresponds

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:21.090
to your brand query.

00:12:21.090 --> 00:12:22.710
That's not quite enough, because
of course, anybody

00:12:22.710 --> 00:12:23.790
could do that.

00:12:23.790 --> 00:12:26.760
The last thing you need to do
is add code your page itself

00:12:26.760 --> 00:12:29.000
that validates that that
page is yours.

00:12:29.000 --> 00:12:30.640
Now there's a number of
different ways to do this, and

00:12:30.640 --> 00:12:33.535
previous talks actually today,
including Paul Linner and

00:12:33.535 --> 00:12:34.340
Chris [? Macinez, ?]

00:12:34.340 --> 00:12:37.970
having to do with our new
Badges, provide some

00:12:37.970 --> 00:12:39.050
techniques to do that.

00:12:39.050 --> 00:12:42.480
The first technique that I'm
going to describe is to add a

00:12:42.480 --> 00:12:43.750
widget to your page.

00:12:43.750 --> 00:12:45.760
And the widget could either be
a Brand Badge, which we see

00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:49.080
here on the right, or a Follow
button, which you also see

00:12:49.080 --> 00:12:49.620
here on the right.

00:12:49.620 --> 00:12:51.940
The Brand Badge is a
beautiful, small

00:12:51.940 --> 00:12:54.280
representation of your +Page
that you can embed

00:12:54.280 --> 00:12:55.400
anywhere on your site.

00:12:55.400 --> 00:12:58.090
But if it happens to be on your
home page, Google search

00:12:58.090 --> 00:12:59.820
crawler will see this
and take that as

00:12:59.820 --> 00:13:01.870
validation of the page itself.

00:13:01.870 --> 00:13:03.520
The same is true for
the Follow button.

00:13:03.520 --> 00:13:05.670
The Follow button is a lighter
weight version of this.

00:13:05.670 --> 00:13:06.890
You'll notice that Follow
exists in the

00:13:06.890 --> 00:13:08.490
Brand Badge as well.

00:13:08.490 --> 00:13:10.930
And Follow provides yet another
way that you can embed

00:13:10.930 --> 00:13:13.690
anywhere in your site, but in
particular, on your claimed

00:13:13.690 --> 00:13:17.090
page, to indicate that the +Page
is yours, and to allow

00:13:17.090 --> 00:13:19.050
users the ability
to establish a

00:13:19.050 --> 00:13:21.240
relationship with you by following.

00:13:21.240 --> 00:13:24.080
And then finally, if none of
these work for your particular

00:13:24.080 --> 00:13:26.990
UX reasons or others, you can
simply just add a link tag,

00:13:26.990 --> 00:13:29.570
which has no UX associated
with it whatsoever, or a

00:13:29.570 --> 00:13:34.570
direct link to your +Page.

00:13:34.570 --> 00:13:37.580
Once Google search crawlers
crawl your page, they will see

00:13:37.580 --> 00:13:40.830
this and take this as
validation, at which point

00:13:40.830 --> 00:13:41.850
you're pretty much done.

00:13:41.850 --> 00:13:43.600
How do you know that
this has happened?

00:13:43.600 --> 00:13:47.960
You go back to your +Page, and
then take note of the URL here

00:13:47.960 --> 00:13:48.910
for TuneIn.

00:13:48.910 --> 00:13:51.260
If there's a small check boxes
just to the right of it,

00:13:51.260 --> 00:13:53.830
Google's crawlers have
found, crawled, and

00:13:53.830 --> 00:13:55.330
validated your page.

00:13:55.330 --> 00:13:56.870
At this point, you're completely
done, and you can

00:13:56.870 --> 00:13:58.890
activate the right hand
search box simply by

00:13:58.890 --> 00:14:02.140
adding Activated Posts--

00:14:02.140 --> 00:14:05.350
excuse me, Active Posts, which
is the last stage in the basic

00:14:05.350 --> 00:14:06.290
integration--

00:14:06.290 --> 00:14:07.150
very simple.

00:14:07.150 --> 00:14:11.300
It's the same as posting a share
or a post your personal

00:14:11.300 --> 00:14:14.510
stream, only, of course, it
corresponds to your +Page.

00:14:14.510 --> 00:14:17.190
Now, there are two requirements
associated with

00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:19.200
posts that are required
to trigger the

00:14:19.200 --> 00:14:20.470
right hand search box.

00:14:20.470 --> 00:14:23.360
The absolute requirement is
that you have some text.

00:14:23.360 --> 00:14:26.630
We need to provide additional
information in context.

00:14:26.630 --> 00:14:28.600
But of course, it is strongly
recommend as well to either

00:14:28.600 --> 00:14:31.680
have a link or an image.

00:14:31.680 --> 00:14:34.890
The image will be displayed
directly on the page,

00:14:34.890 --> 00:14:38.620
providing that it can
be, of course.

00:14:38.620 --> 00:14:43.080
And then if you provide a link,
Google's crawlers will

00:14:43.080 --> 00:14:45.720
crawl that link, find an image
from it, and display that as

00:14:45.720 --> 00:14:48.250
well in the right hand side.

00:14:48.250 --> 00:14:50.220
And here we have a couple
of examples.

00:14:50.220 --> 00:14:54.790
TuneIn is promoting a Deadmau5
concert with a link.

00:14:54.790 --> 00:14:58.420
That link was crawled on
TuneIn's website, and the

00:14:58.420 --> 00:15:00.410
image appeared accordingly.

00:15:00.410 --> 00:15:02.920
In the second particular
example, an image was provided

00:15:02.920 --> 00:15:06.540
directly, which corresponds
to the text.

00:15:09.780 --> 00:15:11.240
And that's pretty much it.

00:15:11.240 --> 00:15:12.270
It's incredibly simple.

00:15:12.270 --> 00:15:15.050
And like I said, your portion
of this can be done in as

00:15:15.050 --> 00:15:18.220
little as 15, 30 minutes today,
simply by starting up

00:15:18.220 --> 00:15:21.550
your +Page, claiming it, and
then providing validation.

00:15:21.550 --> 00:15:23.170
Google search crawlers
will do the rest.

00:15:23.170 --> 00:15:27.120
So before and after is an
incredibly powerful

00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:32.110
demonstration of this technique
and this technology.

00:15:32.110 --> 00:15:33.960
So from here, I'm going to
talk about the deeper

00:15:33.960 --> 00:15:34.470
integration.

00:15:34.470 --> 00:15:36.960
And this is something that, as
Ardan mentioned, is already

00:15:36.960 --> 00:15:38.820
paying dividends, but is
becoming more and more

00:15:38.820 --> 00:15:41.190
powerful as we continue to add
features of the Google+

00:15:41.190 --> 00:15:42.440
Sign-In platform.

00:15:42.440 --> 00:15:45.180
And this involves integrating
Google+ Sign-In, and then

00:15:45.180 --> 00:15:48.220
sending app activities with
users' consent to Google,

00:15:48.220 --> 00:15:51.260
indicating activity that is
going on on your site.

00:15:51.260 --> 00:15:54.120
Now, thinking about this in a
very straightforward fashion,

00:15:54.120 --> 00:15:57.730
if you look at the Popular on
Google+ side, we need to know

00:15:57.730 --> 00:15:59.850
how many users are doing
something, and what they're

00:15:59.850 --> 00:16:01.580
doing, and then to be able
to represent that.

00:16:01.580 --> 00:16:03.660
Corresponds to three concepts.

00:16:03.660 --> 00:16:06.290
First of all, who's
on your site?

00:16:06.290 --> 00:16:12.390
This is conferred by adding
Google+ Sign-In to your site.

00:16:12.390 --> 00:16:14.360
Second, sending app
activities--

00:16:14.360 --> 00:16:17.200
what is the user doing,
and on what page--

00:16:17.200 --> 00:16:20.380
which is represented as a URL,
which we'll see in details--

00:16:20.380 --> 00:16:22.000
does that activity apply?

00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:24.030
And then third, Google's
crawlers

00:16:24.030 --> 00:16:27.270
will crawl those URLs.

00:16:27.270 --> 00:16:30.340
And you can provide a way using
schema.org to tell us

00:16:30.340 --> 00:16:32.580
how to best render that content,
so that when the user

00:16:32.580 --> 00:16:36.380
sees it in Popular on Google+,
will get an accurate

00:16:36.380 --> 00:16:38.750
representation of where
they're about to go.

00:16:38.750 --> 00:16:40.790
Let's dive into the details.

00:16:40.790 --> 00:16:43.220
First thing to do is to
integrate Google+ Sign-In.

00:16:43.220 --> 00:16:46.170
Now, there are a number of
different talks in Google I/O

00:16:46.170 --> 00:16:48.180
today that will give you
a lot of the details .

00:16:48.180 --> 00:16:50.170
And it's important to recognize
that you can do this

00:16:50.170 --> 00:16:54.850
for web, Android, or I/O.
Everything that applies to

00:16:54.850 --> 00:16:59.050
this talk has to do it either
web- or app-related

00:16:59.050 --> 00:17:00.450
activities.

00:17:00.450 --> 00:17:02.570
For the purposes of the
discussion today, I'm going to

00:17:02.570 --> 00:17:06.190
go through the web flow just
as an example, just to show

00:17:06.190 --> 00:17:07.220
you how simple it will be.

00:17:07.220 --> 00:17:10.000
However, there are a number of
different talks, all of which

00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:10.630
are tomorrow--

00:17:10.630 --> 00:17:14.460
a deep dive into integration on
web, Android, and iOS-- and

00:17:14.460 --> 00:17:16.666
I strongly encourage you to
check out any of them if they

00:17:16.666 --> 00:17:18.640
are of interest to you.

00:17:18.640 --> 00:17:20.630
So the first thing to do in
integrating to a Google+

00:17:20.630 --> 00:17:22.140
Sign-In into a webpage
is to add the

00:17:22.140 --> 00:17:23.859
Google+ JavaScript snippet.

00:17:23.859 --> 00:17:27.490
And this activates all APIs
that Google+ supports.

00:17:27.490 --> 00:17:31.220
This includes +1, Brand
Badge, Follow widget.

00:17:31.220 --> 00:17:35.000
It also allows you access to the
Google+ Client, with which

00:17:35.000 --> 00:17:37.920
you can send activities
to Google.

00:17:37.920 --> 00:17:40.250
It's a pretty straightforward
piece of boilerplate that you

00:17:40.250 --> 00:17:42.000
more or less just copy
and paste once

00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:43.380
onto any given page.

00:17:43.380 --> 00:17:45.500
And then from there, what you
would like to do is add a

00:17:45.500 --> 00:17:47.780
Google+ Sign-In widget.

00:17:47.780 --> 00:17:50.070
The widget is activated, as
all other widgets on the

00:17:50.070 --> 00:17:54.420
Google+ platform are, with a
small snippet of HTML5 markup.

00:17:54.420 --> 00:17:58.060
This provides an example
of the Sign-In widget.

00:17:58.060 --> 00:18:00.160
As you'll notice, it's
simply just a span

00:18:00.160 --> 00:18:02.250
which has a class g-signin.

00:18:02.250 --> 00:18:04.960
All widgets have class equals
g dash something.

00:18:04.960 --> 00:18:06.740
And in this case, it's
a Sign-In widget.

00:18:06.740 --> 00:18:08.620
I'll go through a couple of the
other parameters that are

00:18:08.620 --> 00:18:11.930
relevant to this integration,
as well as all integrations

00:18:11.930 --> 00:18:14.260
that have to do with Sign-In,
just to give you a little more

00:18:14.260 --> 00:18:17.450
flavor for the important factors
that are involved in

00:18:17.450 --> 00:18:18.600
integration.

00:18:18.600 --> 00:18:21.990
And the first one is the
callback parameter.

00:18:21.990 --> 00:18:25.310
In the case of web, when a user
goes through a Sign-In

00:18:25.310 --> 00:18:28.140
flow, a JavaScript function
is executed with the

00:18:28.140 --> 00:18:29.460
result of that flow.

00:18:29.460 --> 00:18:32.100
And what you need to know
is simply one thing.

00:18:32.100 --> 00:18:33.180
Was it successful?

00:18:33.180 --> 00:18:35.930
And if it was successful, at
that point, you can start

00:18:35.930 --> 00:18:38.960
sending app activities
back to Google.

00:18:38.960 --> 00:18:40.490
Let's take a look at
what the JavaScript

00:18:40.490 --> 00:18:41.180
function will look like.

00:18:41.180 --> 00:18:42.150
This is very simple.

00:18:42.150 --> 00:18:43.810
And of course, we can
go into more detail.

00:18:43.810 --> 00:18:47.650
I recommend that you go to the
web talk tomorrow, or watch it

00:18:47.650 --> 00:18:49.320
on stream if you'd like.

00:18:49.320 --> 00:18:50.530
Here, we're defining
a function called

00:18:50.530 --> 00:18:51.440
handleAuthResult.

00:18:51.440 --> 00:18:53.350
It takes in a result object.

00:18:53.350 --> 00:18:55.880
For the purposes of the
function, it simply just looks

00:18:55.880 --> 00:18:57.670
like a standard object.

00:18:57.670 --> 00:18:59.400
And it either has as
one of two fields.

00:18:59.400 --> 00:19:00.520
Access token--

00:19:00.520 --> 00:19:05.820
if that token exists, the flow
was executed successfully, and

00:19:05.820 --> 00:19:07.920
you can start making requests,
which we indicate here via

00:19:07.920 --> 00:19:08.960
simple Boolean.

00:19:08.960 --> 00:19:10.540
There's a number of
ways to do that.

00:19:10.540 --> 00:19:12.630
If there's an error, you can log
it, and there's a number

00:19:12.630 --> 00:19:14.560
of different other things that
you can do, which you can hear

00:19:14.560 --> 00:19:15.990
about tomorrow.

00:19:15.990 --> 00:19:18.360
Second field is Client ID.

00:19:18.360 --> 00:19:21.340
Your application or site needs
to be able to identify itself

00:19:21.340 --> 00:19:26.590
to Google uniquely so that
we know what app or site

00:19:26.590 --> 00:19:28.590
corresponds to the activities.

00:19:28.590 --> 00:19:32.100
And that's done through the
use of a Client ID.

00:19:32.100 --> 00:19:37.090
You can set up your Client ID
at cloud.google.com/console,

00:19:37.090 --> 00:19:39.620
and then click Register App.

00:19:39.620 --> 00:19:42.530
You'll go through a flow, of
which I've shown a couple of

00:19:42.530 --> 00:19:45.850
details here, that allows you
to select the type of app or

00:19:45.850 --> 00:19:49.180
site that you're talking about,
and then add certain

00:19:49.180 --> 00:19:50.860
metadata associated with it.

00:19:50.860 --> 00:19:53.190
In the case of a web
application, all you need to

00:19:53.190 --> 00:19:56.530
do is indicate that it is a web
application, and then copy

00:19:56.530 --> 00:20:00.010
and paste in all the host
origins on which

00:20:00.010 --> 00:20:02.150
your script may exist.

00:20:02.150 --> 00:20:05.500
Between the two of these,
Google's APIs will be able to

00:20:05.500 --> 00:20:08.180
validate that the client ID is
legitimate, and then therefore

00:20:08.180 --> 00:20:12.570
know who your app is
and who you are.

00:20:12.570 --> 00:20:14.950
Finally, I'll talk about this
requestvisibleactions field

00:20:14.950 --> 00:20:18.260
just to call out again that all
these activities that you

00:20:18.260 --> 00:20:21.170
post on behalf of your users are
done with their consent.

00:20:21.170 --> 00:20:23.720
When you pass
requestvisibleactions equals

00:20:23.720 --> 00:20:29.030
this value to Google, what it
does is triggers the consent

00:20:29.030 --> 00:20:32.100
dialogue to ask the user, is
it all right for us to send

00:20:32.100 --> 00:20:34.010
activities on your behalf?

00:20:34.010 --> 00:20:37.320
Supposing they consent, your
JavaScript callback will get

00:20:37.320 --> 00:20:38.220
an access token.

00:20:38.220 --> 00:20:41.306
And from there you can start
sending activities.

00:20:41.306 --> 00:20:43.820
So finally, let's talk about
what it looks like to actually

00:20:43.820 --> 00:20:44.760
send those activities.

00:20:44.760 --> 00:20:47.410
And this is also very simple,
so simple that the amount of

00:20:47.410 --> 00:20:49.530
JavaScript necessary can
fit on one slide with

00:20:49.530 --> 00:20:51.160
fairly large text.

00:20:51.160 --> 00:20:52.750
There are two pieces associated
with this.

00:20:52.750 --> 00:20:56.110
One, there's a simple "if"
conditional that says, was the

00:20:56.110 --> 00:20:57.800
sign-in flow successful
to begin with?

00:20:57.800 --> 00:20:59.480
And there's a number of
different pieces of logic you

00:20:59.480 --> 00:21:01.780
can put in there, depending
on your integration.

00:21:01.780 --> 00:21:04.860
But most importantly,
you create a moment.

00:21:04.860 --> 00:21:08.140
The Google Moments API allows
you to send different types of

00:21:08.140 --> 00:21:10.930
what we call moments-- in this
particular case, an activity--

00:21:10.930 --> 00:21:11.880
to Google.

00:21:11.880 --> 00:21:14.340
There are only two pieces of
data associated with an

00:21:14.340 --> 00:21:17.460
activity that are absolutely
required-- one, the type.

00:21:17.460 --> 00:21:19.520
There are a number of
different types.

00:21:19.520 --> 00:21:22.062
In this particular example,
I'm saying the user has

00:21:22.062 --> 00:21:24.570
listened to something,
and that something is

00:21:24.570 --> 00:21:26.060
identified by a URL.

00:21:26.060 --> 00:21:27.540
And that's all it is.

00:21:27.540 --> 00:21:31.330
From there, you use the Google
Client, which already has the

00:21:31.330 --> 00:21:34.290
access token which has been
granted by the user going

00:21:34.290 --> 00:21:36.130
through the consent
flow to it.

00:21:36.130 --> 00:21:38.810
And you simply just post this to
the moments vault, which is

00:21:38.810 --> 00:21:40.770
the URL for the moments API.

00:21:40.770 --> 00:21:43.710
From there, Google knows that
the activity has occurred, and

00:21:43.710 --> 00:21:44.930
you're pretty much done.

00:21:44.930 --> 00:21:47.680
The result of this can
be used as well, for

00:21:47.680 --> 00:21:48.750
logging and other purposes.

00:21:48.750 --> 00:21:51.370
But for the purposes of Popular
on Google+, that is

00:21:51.370 --> 00:21:54.350
all you need to do.

00:21:54.350 --> 00:21:56.920
So at this point, if we go back
to the Popular on Google+

00:21:56.920 --> 00:22:00.150
section, let's think about it.

00:22:00.150 --> 00:22:01.060
What do we know how to do?

00:22:01.060 --> 00:22:04.680
We know who's doing what on
your site, and to what.

00:22:04.680 --> 00:22:08.370
So we can display the account,
basically by

00:22:08.370 --> 00:22:10.290
uniquifying the URLs.

00:22:10.290 --> 00:22:13.750
And we know that that
number of users has

00:22:13.750 --> 00:22:14.900
performed that activity.

00:22:14.900 --> 00:22:19.120
The last piece of data that we
need is data about what that

00:22:19.120 --> 00:22:20.920
URL actually corresponds to.

00:22:20.920 --> 00:22:26.680
And the way that we do that is
by requesting that sites add

00:22:26.680 --> 00:22:28.430
schema.org markup
to their page.

00:22:28.430 --> 00:22:31.880
Now, schema.org is an open
standard that simply just

00:22:31.880 --> 00:22:35.350
involves adding additional
attributes to existing HTML to

00:22:35.350 --> 00:22:37.790
tell us more about what it is,
semantically speaking.

00:22:37.790 --> 00:22:42.420
Now, Google is really good at
inferring meaning from HTML.

00:22:42.420 --> 00:22:46.470
But at the same time, schema.org
allows you to

00:22:46.470 --> 00:22:49.790
specifically indicate what
that content is.

00:22:49.790 --> 00:22:50.920
Is it a song?

00:22:50.920 --> 00:22:52.220
What is its duration?

00:22:52.220 --> 00:22:53.770
What language are we
talking about?

00:22:53.770 --> 00:22:55.650
It basically takes the guesswork
out, and really

00:22:55.650 --> 00:22:57.840
makes it much more
deterministic.

00:22:57.840 --> 00:22:59.860
And it's an incredibly
powerful technique.

00:22:59.860 --> 00:23:04.190
But I will start by talking
about a simple example here,

00:23:04.190 --> 00:23:06.040
corresponding to a song.

00:23:06.040 --> 00:23:07.360
Now, take a look
at this markup.

00:23:07.360 --> 00:23:08.680
It's very simple.

00:23:08.680 --> 00:23:11.590
Obviously, it would be more
complex, in all likelihood, on

00:23:11.590 --> 00:23:14.010
a real site, but it really
gets the point across.

00:23:14.010 --> 00:23:18.480
This represents a displayed
representation of a song.

00:23:18.480 --> 00:23:19.930
You can see there's an image.

00:23:19.930 --> 00:23:24.390
There's the BBC Radio 93.5 is
